m_q.target_metric: Total number of fraud reports submitted via FTC web interface between 2022 and 2024
filters: Data Contributor contains 'FTC - Web Reports' and 'Fraud'
Exclude IDT (Identity Theft) reports, include only Fraud & Other
sub_questions: Which file contains FTC web fraud reports?
How to identify web-based fraud reports vs other report types?
What is the distinction between 'Fraud & Other' and 'IDT' in the data?
Should IDT be included in fraud count or excluded?
What are the report counts for each year (2022, 2023, 2024)?

format_notes: Percentage values stored as strings with '%' suffix
Data Contributor column uses parenthetical notation to specify report type: (IDT) or (Fraud & Other)
FTC reports are categorized by collection method: Web Reports, Mobile Reports, phone-based reports

constraints: Year must be between 2022 and 2024 inclusive
Data Contributor must match pattern 'FTC - Web Reports (Fraud & Other)'
# of Reports must be non-negative integer
derived_filters: Filter rows where Data Contributor == 'FTC - Web Reports (Fraud & Other)'
output_format_requirements: Return single integer value representing sum of fraud reports
Sum # of Reports column across filtered rows
